Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_ml(25.10)                                                  init_ml(25.10)

Name
       init_ml - Initializes the environment to start writing data for JedAI

Syntax
       init_ml

       [-help]

       [-comment <string>]

       [-flow_phase <string>]

       [-name <string>]

       -prefix <string>

       [-scenario <string>]

       Initializes  the  environment to start writing data for JedAI. Run this
       command before using any of the following commands to ensure that  con-
       tent is properly labeled for big data ingestion and registration:

              * write_ml_design

              * write_ml_library

              * write_ml_timing_graph

              * write_ml_timing_path

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each init_ml parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man init_ml.

       -comment <string>
              Specifies a comment.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -flow_phase <string>
              Specifies the flow phase.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -name <string>
              Specifies the design name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -prefix <string>
              Specifies the prefix for the output files.

              Data_type: string, required

       -scenario <string>
              Specifies the scenario.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
              * The following command the environment to  start  writing  data
                for JedAI for the cts flow phase with the default scenario for
                the dtmf design.

                init_ml  -prefix out/ -name dtmf -flow_phase cts -scenario de-
                fault -comment "This is a demo."

Related Information
              * write_ml_design

              * write_ml_library

              * write_ml_timing_graph

              * write_ml_timing_path

